DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-0.089ft at 10:06\n-2.97ft at 13:06\n\nOBSERVATION:\nO
 ld SSW swell starts the day off small: knee-thigh-waist high\, and drained
  by an early morning negative low tide. A fresh pulse of mid-period WNW sw
 ell fills in during the day\, potentially setting up waist to chest high+ 
 surf over the afternoon\, largest late. \n\nLight S/SE early\, but overnig
 ht southerly winds look to make for a lumpy start. Even worse conditions d
 ue in the afternoon from breezy to strong S/SSE wind.
